#. type: Title -
#, no-wrap
msgid "Overwriting Configurations\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"The persistent storage allows you to overwrite the configuration of the "
"programs included in Tails. Those programs are carefully configured with "
"security in mind.  Overwriting the default configuration can break this "
"security or render them unusuable."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Furthermore, the anonymity of Tor and Tails relies on making it harder to\n"
"distinguish one Tails user from another. <strong>Changing the default\n"
"configurations can break your anonymity.</strong>\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title -
#, no-wrap
msgid "Installing New Software\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"The programs included in Tails are selected with care and audited for their "
"security. This may not be the case of all the packages available in Debian.  "
"**Other programs than the ones included in Tails may be subject to security "
"holes that Tails do not protect you from.**"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title -
#, no-wrap
msgid "Browser Plugins\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
msgid ""
"The web browser is a central part in a system like Tails. The plugins "
"included in the browser are carefully chosen and configured with security in "
"mind. **If you install other plugins or change their configuration, you can "
"break your anonymity.**"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title -
#, no-wrap
msgid "Use to the Minimum\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"**Use the persistent storage only when necessary and to the minimum.** It is\n"
"always possible to start Tails without activating the permanent storage. All the\n"
"features of the permanent storage are optional and need to be explicitly\n"
"activated. Only the files that you specify are stored.\n"
msgstr ""
